===Etymology===
Compare French ''[[achèvement]]'', English [[hatchment]]
===Noun===
#The act of [[achieving]] or performing; an obtaining by exertion; [[successful]] performance; [[accomplishment]]; as, the '''achievement''' of his object.
# A great or heroic deed; something accomplished by [[valor]], [[boldness]], or [[praiseworthy]] exertion; a feat.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*[The exploits] of the ancient saints ... do far surpass the most famous '''achievements''' of pagan heroes. - [[Barrow]]
#:*The highest '''achievements''' of the human intellect. - [[Macaulay]]
#''(Heraldry):'' An [[escutcheon]] or [[ensign]] [[armorial]]; now generally applied to the funeral shield commonly called [[hatchment]]. - [[Cussans]]

